# ==============================================================================
# Render-scope local declarations — `code = expr` is a binding, not a textnode
# ==============================================================================
# Regression: `name = expr` inside a render block used to fall through
# emitNode's general-expression path and become `createTextNode(String((name
# = expr)))`, which both leaks an undeclared global and inserts a stray
# textnode into the DOM. A subsequent `span name` reference (when `name` is
# also an HTML tag like `code`) was treated as a nested element instead of a
# value read. The fix: treat `(= ident expr)` as a JS local declaration in
# the surrounding factory scope, and let lexical bindings shadow HTML tag
# names in subsequent references.

code "render-local binding compiles to a hoisted `let`, not a textnode", '''
